'''ISO 3166-2:SL''' code for the [[provinces of Sierra Leone]]. The purpose of this family of standards is to establish a worldwide series of short abbreviations for places, for use on package labels, containers and such. Anywhere where a short alphanumeric code can serve to clearly indicate a location in a more convenient and less ambiguous form than the full place name. 

== Provinces (13) ==
* SL-E	[[Eastern Province, Sierra Leone|Eastern]]
* SL-N	[[Northern Province, Sierra Leone|Northern]]
* SL-S	[[Southern Province, Sierra Leone|Southern]]
* SL-W	[[Western Area, Sierra Leone|Western Area (Freetown)]]

